msub></math></span></span>.</p><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Student <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> says that the torque is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"tau equals L sub 0, end sub, F sub 0, end sub, the sine of theta sub 0\"><math alttext=\"tau equals L sub 0, end sub, F sub 0, end sub, the sine of theta sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>τ</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi>sin</mi><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span>.</p><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Student <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> says that the torque is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"tau equals r sub perpendicular, end sub, F sub 0\"><math alttext=\"tau equals r sub perpendicular, end sub, F sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>τ</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mo>⊥</mo></msub><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span>.</p><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following provides valid reasoning to justify which student or students is (are) correct?</p>\n",
